Ingredients.4: 1 pinch seasoned salt, or to taste

Ingredients.5: 1 pinch garlic and herb seasoning blend (such as Mrs. Dash®), or to taste

Directions.1: Preheat an outdoor grill for medium-high heat.

Directions.2: Place walleye, skin-side down, in the center of one aluminum foil square. Brush fillet with butter; season with seasoned salt and garlic and herb seasoning blend. Place second aluminum foil square over the fish and fold edges of the two pieces of foil together to form a secure packet.

Directions.3: Cook on the preheated grill until fish flakes easily with a fork, about 7 minutes per side.
